1
00:01:11,559 --> 00:01:12,519
According to what you're saying,

2
00:01:12,919 --> 00:01:14,519
the gradual decline of Feimanchi

3
00:01:14,959 --> 00:01:17,000
is due to Chairman Gu Rongchen's

4
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:17,440
mismanagement?

5
00:01:17,440 --> 00:01:18,000
That's right.

6
00:01:18,599 --> 00:01:20,519
A company with over 30% debt,

7
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:22,319
how could it operate normally?

8
00:01:22,919 --> 00:01:23,959
If the former executives hadn't

9
00:01:24,160 --> 00:01:25,480
blindly expanded branch offices,

10
00:01:26,040 --> 00:01:27,599
Feimanchi wouldn't be like this now.

11
00:01:28,360 --> 00:01:28,959
Mr. Gu,

12
00:01:29,400 --> 00:01:31,160
the next question might be a bit sensitive.

13
00:01:31,519 --> 00:01:32,279
Is that okay?

14
00:01:32,480 --> 00:01:33,160
How sensitive?

15
00:01:33,919 --> 00:01:35,440
Should I take an

16
00:01:35,440 --> 00:01:36,279
allergy pill beforehand?

17
00:01:39,199 --> 00:01:40,120
Just kidding.

18
00:01:40,839 --> 00:01:41,879
Not funny, Secretary Lin?

19
00:01:44,519 --> 00:01:45,000
Please continue.

20
00:01:45,800 --> 00:01:47,199
The founder of Feimanchi,

21
00:01:47,480 --> 00:01:49,120
former Chairman Gu Rongtao,

22
00:01:49,360 --> 00:01:51,639
was exposed in an embezzlement scandal over a decade ago.

23
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:53,040
Now, the current Chairman,

24
00:01:53,040 --> 00:01:53,919
Mr. Gu Rongchen,

25
00:01:54,160 --> 00:01:55,519
is also facing suspicions regarding his management.

26
00:01:55,839 --> 00:01:57,800
Are you sure your acquisition this time

27
00:01:57,800 --> 00:01:59,599
is entirely based on commercial considerations?

28
00:02:02,199 --> 00:02:02,919
Mr. Gu.

29
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:11,399
I just want to say one thing here.

30
00:02:12,119 --> 00:02:13,720
My father, Mr. Gu Rongtao,

31
00:02:14,559 --> 00:02:15,440
never did anything

32
00:02:15,679 --> 00:02:17,039
to let Feimanchi down.

33
00:02:19,600 --> 00:02:20,479
As for everything else,

34
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:22,880
I have nothing to answer.

35
00:02:35,279 --> 00:02:37,000
We're at my place before I knew it.

36
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:39,399
Mr. Gu,

37
00:02:40,320 --> 00:02:41,399
you've been busy all day.

38
00:02:41,759 --> 00:02:42,479
Aren't you tired?

39
00:02:43,240 --> 00:02:44,240
You just kept following me.

40
00:02:44,600 --> 00:02:46,080
Everything is inevitable.

41
00:02:47,919 --> 00:02:50,080
What happened to Feimanchi over the past 20 years

42
00:02:52,360 --> 00:02:53,880
was perhaps bound to happen.

43
00:02:54,440 --> 00:02:55,360
I often think,

44
00:02:57,919 --> 00:02:59,160
maybe my father

45
00:03:00,360 --> 00:03:01,479
was too idealistic.

46
00:03:03,399 --> 00:03:04,080
Mr. Gu,

47
00:03:04,679 --> 00:03:05,960
don't blame your father.

48
00:03:06,320 --> 00:03:07,720
The one who should truly feel guilty

49
00:03:07,919 --> 00:03:08,880
should be me.

50
00:03:11,440 --> 00:03:12,360
Because my father...

51
00:03:14,600 --> 00:03:16,479
Anyone who's been to Tongzhou Factory knows

52
00:03:17,919 --> 00:03:19,520
what a great person he must be

53
00:03:20,479 --> 00:03:22,119
to build such a beautiful place.

54
00:03:24,679 --> 00:03:25,960
But my father...

55
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:26,600
Stop talking.

56
00:03:28,279 --> 00:03:29,479
I don't want to discuss this.

57
00:03:30,160 --> 00:03:31,880
If you want to go to Tongzhou Factory,

58
00:03:32,839 --> 00:03:34,039
I can take you to see it.

59
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:36,759
Don't bother.

60
00:03:37,919 --> 00:03:39,000
I don't want to go at all.

61
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:41,520
Actually, you're not a bad person.

62
00:03:42,520 --> 00:03:43,839
You're just a heartbroken person.

63
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:47,080
Even though you wield great power

64
00:03:48,160 --> 00:03:49,440
and make many people fear you,

65
00:03:51,080 --> 00:03:52,240
deep down,

66
00:03:54,199 --> 00:03:55,759
you're just someone who, at nine,

67
00:03:56,559 --> 00:03:57,720
stopped growing,

68
00:03:58,039 --> 00:03:59,240
a sick child.

69
00:04:05,479 --> 00:04:06,800
What do you think

70
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:08,000
is your greatest strength?

71
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:10,000
Your fiance loved you so much,

72
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:13,199
what exactly did he love about you?

73
00:04:14,440 --> 00:04:15,919
I remember he told me

74
00:04:17,760 --> 00:04:18,920
that being with me

75
00:04:20,920 --> 00:04:22,200
is like revolving in an orbit.

76
00:04:23,040 --> 00:04:24,679
The Earth revolves around the sun,

77
00:04:26,679 --> 00:04:27,920
and will never leave the sun.

78
00:04:28,799 --> 00:04:29,440
Right.

79
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:34,079
Actually, I know everything now.

80
00:04:35,760 --> 00:04:37,079
The house I'm living in now

81
00:04:37,880 --> 00:04:39,440
has a special meaning to you.

82
00:04:40,279 --> 00:04:41,279
The day I moved into my new place,

83
00:04:42,399 --> 00:04:43,399
you didn't come when I invited you.

84
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:45,920
Maybe that was the reason.

85
00:04:49,959 --> 00:04:51,320
I've figured it out now.

86
00:04:53,799 --> 00:04:55,559
It's just a house, after all.

87
00:04:57,640 --> 00:04:58,519
What's important

88
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:01,119
isn't where you live,

89
00:05:03,160 --> 00:05:04,640
but who you live with.

90
00:05:07,519 --> 00:05:08,160
So,

91
00:05:09,880 --> 00:05:10,799
you don't need to worry.

92
00:05:11,559 --> 00:05:12,839
I've already let it go.

93
00:05:26,440 --> 00:05:27,200
What is it?

94
00:05:27,399 --> 00:05:28,720
That you had to come to my house this early?

95
00:05:29,119 --> 00:05:30,000
Couldn't we talk at the office?

96
00:05:30,559 --> 00:05:31,200
No.

97
00:05:34,640 --> 00:05:35,200
Tell me.

98
00:05:36,040 --> 00:05:38,119
Secretary Lin Jiaqi's daily whereabouts.

99
00:05:38,440 --> 00:05:39,559
Did you send someone to monitor her?

100
00:05:41,239 --> 00:05:41,920
No.

101
00:05:42,239 --> 00:05:43,119
I didn't think it was necessary.

102
00:05:43,480 --> 00:05:44,239
Nelson.

103
00:05:45,359 --> 00:05:46,920
Is your brain fried, darn it?

104
00:05:48,119 --> 00:05:49,880
You forgot even the most basic rules?

105
00:05:51,559 --> 00:05:53,079
What do you mean by necessary?

106
00:05:53,440 --> 00:05:54,600
Let me ask you, when have we ever

107
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:55,359
done it because it was necessary

108
00:05:55,359 --> 00:05:56,359
when monitoring others?

109
00:05:57,079 --> 00:05:58,640
Whether it's despicable or shameless,

110
00:05:59,200 --> 00:06:00,559
this is what doing our kind of work

111
00:06:00,559 --> 00:06:01,880
absolutely requires.

112
00:06:02,559 --> 00:06:04,480
Why are you so angry this early in the morning?

113
00:06:05,160 --> 00:06:05,799
Want some coffee?

114
00:06:06,320 --> 00:06:07,000
No.

115
00:06:10,119 --> 00:06:10,880
Let me ask you.

116
00:06:12,040 --> 00:06:14,160
Did Gu Rongchen go on a business trip to Japan today?

117
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:15,160
Yes.

118
00:06:15,640 --> 00:06:17,519
There seems to be an executive meeting in Dong Jing.

119
00:06:17,760 --> 00:06:18,279
What's wrong?

120
00:06:22,119 --> 00:06:23,000
Let me tell you.

121
00:06:23,880 --> 00:06:26,160
There is no so-called executive meeting at all.

122
00:06:27,200 --> 00:06:29,399
Not only is this business trip excuse made up,

123
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:30,920
but the Directors here,

124
00:06:30,920 --> 00:06:33,359
not a single one knows Gu Rongchen's whereabouts.

125
00:06:35,839 --> 00:06:37,359
Do you know what this means?

126
00:06:41,119 --> 00:06:42,399
I was afraid you'd be careless.

127
00:06:43,720 --> 00:06:44,720
Good thing I got someone

128
00:06:44,720 --> 00:06:46,519
to keep an eye on his house in the Wanhao district.

129
00:06:47,040 --> 00:06:48,040
Do you know who has been

130
00:06:48,040 --> 00:06:49,760
showing up there all this time?

131
00:06:51,559 --> 00:06:52,640
Lin Jiaqi.

132
00:06:53,519 --> 00:06:54,239
During this time,

133
00:06:54,239 --> 00:06:56,079
the one who's been covering for Gu Rongchen

134
00:06:56,079 --> 00:06:57,519
is your Secretary Lin.

135
00:07:01,200 --> 00:07:01,720
Hello.

136
00:07:01,839 --> 00:07:02,600
Mrs. Gu.

137
00:07:03,799 --> 00:07:04,519
Jiaqi.

138
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:06,040
This matter,

139
00:07:06,040 --> 00:07:07,679
must absolutely not be known by anyone.

140
00:07:07,679 --> 00:07:08,640
It must be done in secret.

141
00:08:03,640 --> 00:08:05,880
Sir, this ward does not receive outsiders.

142
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:07,480
Who are you?

143
00:08:08,600 --> 00:08:10,399
We don't receive outsiders here. Please go back.

144
00:08:13,480 --> 00:08:13,959
You...

145
00:08:14,480 --> 00:08:15,640
Sir, you can't go in.

146
00:08:15,640 --> 00:08:16,160
Sir!

147
00:08:16,160 --> 00:08:17,480
CEO Gu, you can't go in.

148
00:08:18,200 --> 00:08:18,920
Rongchen.

149
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:20,320
Open the door quickly.

150
00:08:29,760 --> 00:08:30,359
Dad.

151
00:08:31,119 --> 00:08:31,959
Slow down, Dad.

152
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:33,799
Dad.

153
00:08:52,239 --> 00:08:52,880
Tell me.

154
00:08:54,640 --> 00:08:56,080
What exactly is Gu Rongchen's situation now?

155
00:09:02,440 --> 00:09:03,280
Colon cancer.

156
00:09:05,640 --> 00:09:06,919
He had surgery five years ago.

157
00:09:07,640 --> 00:09:08,599
Now it has relapsed.

158
00:09:09,599 --> 00:09:10,599
Can he have surgery again?

159
00:09:11,119 --> 00:09:11,919
No.

160
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:15,159
The cancer cell spread has reached the kidneys

161
00:09:15,880 --> 00:09:16,960
and other organs.

162
00:09:17,880 --> 00:09:19,039
Especially the kidneys.

163
00:09:20,679 --> 00:09:22,039
That's why he has urinary incontinence.

164
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:27,880
Then why did you hide this from me and do all this for him?

165
00:09:28,760 --> 00:09:30,080
Mrs. Gu asked me to.

166
00:09:31,159 --> 00:09:32,880
She also asked me to bring Xiaoxian over.

167
00:09:34,039 --> 00:09:35,559
In the Chairman's current condition,

168
00:09:36,679 --> 00:09:37,760
the person he wants to see the most

169
00:09:38,320 --> 00:09:39,559
should be his son.

170
00:09:41,919 --> 00:09:42,919
Putting myself in his shoes,

171
00:09:43,359 --> 00:09:44,599
my dad is gone too.

172
00:09:45,479 --> 00:09:46,799
I can understand how he feels.

173
00:09:47,760 --> 00:09:48,599
Besides,

174
00:09:50,320 --> 00:09:51,880
I'm also doing this for the company.

175
00:09:52,039 --> 00:09:53,200
For the Tongzhou Factory.

176
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:55,280
Once the Chairman's condition is made public,

177
00:09:56,200 --> 00:09:58,080
the company will definitely fall into chaos.

178
00:09:58,799 --> 00:10:00,400
The Tongzhou Factory will be completely lost.

179
00:10:01,479 --> 00:10:02,679
So no matter what,

180
00:10:03,760 --> 00:10:04,960
I have to stop this from happening.

181
00:10:05,679 --> 00:10:06,440
Lin Jiaqi.

182
00:10:09,080 --> 00:10:10,400
What exactly does that factory

183
00:10:10,400 --> 00:10:11,359
mean to you?

184
00:10:12,159 --> 00:10:14,440
The memories my lover left me are there.

185
00:10:17,479 --> 00:10:18,919
Then I'm sorry, Lin Jiaqi.

186
00:10:20,719 --> 00:10:22,559
I only have numbers in my head.

187
00:10:23,719 --> 00:10:25,320
I only think about how Gu Rongchen's death

188
00:10:25,320 --> 00:10:27,200
will bring huge losses to the company.

189
00:10:28,159 --> 00:10:29,039
Stock crashes,

190
00:10:29,559 --> 00:10:30,359
bond sell-offs.

191
00:10:31,640 --> 00:10:32,359
As for other things,

192
00:10:33,679 --> 00:10:34,799
I probably don't care.

193
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:46,679
Really?

194
00:10:47,840 --> 00:10:49,880
Gu Rongchen was admitted to the cancer center?

195
00:10:50,559 --> 00:10:51,359
Of course it's true.

196
00:10:51,960 --> 00:10:53,239
Since he's hiding,

197
00:10:53,840 --> 00:10:56,440
his condition must be grim.

198
00:10:57,359 --> 00:10:59,119
It seems things have gotten simpler.

199
00:10:59,440 --> 00:11:00,280
So,

200
00:11:00,840 --> 00:11:01,960
I don't plan to wait anymore.

201
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:03,760
What do you mean?

202
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:06,280
My reward.

203
00:11:07,039 --> 00:11:08,400
It's time you fulfilled your promise.

204
00:11:10,159 --> 00:11:10,840
Okay.

205
00:11:11,119 --> 00:11:11,880
What do you want to do?

206
00:11:14,080 --> 00:11:15,479
I'm going to do what I have to do.

207
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:17,239
A coup is launched when the enemy

208
00:11:17,239 --> 00:11:18,440
is asleep.

209
00:11:20,159 --> 00:11:21,760
I want you to help me today

210
00:11:22,400 --> 00:11:23,640
to sideline Gu Rongchen.

211
00:11:24,840 --> 00:11:25,960
Directors,

212
00:11:26,559 --> 00:11:27,719
have you ever thought about

213
00:11:28,119 --> 00:11:29,640
a change at the top?

214
00:11:31,320 --> 00:11:32,280
What are you talking about?

215
00:11:32,640 --> 00:11:34,400
If this reaches the Chairman's ears...

216
00:11:34,400 --> 00:11:36,239
I'm afraid the Chairman won't hear it.

217
00:11:37,840 --> 00:11:38,960
You all heard me right.

218
00:11:39,520 --> 00:11:40,719
That's exactly what I mean.

219
00:11:41,359 --> 00:11:42,039
Switch sides.

220
00:11:42,960 --> 00:11:43,719
Do it now.

221
00:11:44,119 --> 00:11:45,119
Leave the Chairman

222
00:11:45,520 --> 00:11:46,679
and join Rosenmoss.

223
00:11:48,640 --> 00:11:49,400
Feng Ziang,

224
00:11:50,159 --> 00:11:51,599
do you know what you're saying?

225
00:11:53,640 --> 00:11:54,559
But that's fine.

226
00:11:55,080 --> 00:11:56,400
When the Chairman returns,

227
00:11:56,880 --> 00:11:58,919
I'll be the first to tell him.

228
00:11:59,799 --> 00:12:00,520
Go.

229
00:12:02,159 --> 00:12:04,159
Go check the Taikang Hospital Cancer Center.

230
00:12:05,080 --> 00:12:05,840
The Chairman

231
00:12:06,359 --> 00:12:08,080
should be in a hospital bed right now.

232
00:12:09,159 --> 00:12:10,599
I regret to inform you all

233
00:12:11,280 --> 00:12:12,799
that the Chairman has colon cancer.

234
00:12:13,679 --> 00:12:14,719
It's already in the late stages.

235
00:12:15,840 --> 00:12:17,599
His condition from the surgery five years ago recently worsened.

236
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:18,760
I'm afraid

237
00:12:19,200 --> 00:12:19,960
he won't live past three months.

238
00:12:20,280 --> 00:12:21,960
By then, Feimanchi being acquired

239
00:12:22,880 --> 00:12:24,119
is just a matter of time, isn't it?

240
00:12:34,760 --> 00:12:35,359
Mr. Gu,

241
00:12:37,400 --> 00:12:38,159
take a look.

242
00:12:45,960 --> 00:12:46,679
What's going on?

243
00:12:54,400 --> 00:12:55,599
An emergency Board of Directors meeting?

244
00:12:57,960 --> 00:12:59,080
The Chairman isn't even here.

245
00:12:59,960 --> 00:13:01,039
What kind of board meeting is this?

246
00:13:06,119 --> 00:13:07,280
Even if we switch sides,

247
00:13:07,840 --> 00:13:09,719
who can guarantee that Rosenmoss

248
00:13:09,960 --> 00:13:11,119
will let us keep our equity?

249
00:13:11,440 --> 00:13:13,000
And that we won't be kicked out in the end?

250
00:13:13,520 --> 00:13:14,400
Regarding that,

251
00:13:14,520 --> 00:13:15,760
I can assure everyone.

252
00:13:16,280 --> 00:13:18,479
Rosenmoss and I have reached an agreement.

253
00:13:19,359 --> 00:13:21,280
We will maximize the protection of your interests.

254
00:13:22,960 --> 00:13:24,239
Why should we trust you?

255
00:13:31,559 --> 00:13:33,599
On behalf of Rosenmoss, I assure you all,

256
00:13:34,840 --> 00:13:36,719
as long as you are willing to follow Mr. Feng

257
00:13:37,159 --> 00:13:39,119
and sideline Chairman Gu Rongchen,

258
00:13:39,799 --> 00:13:41,520
then the rights and interests in your hands

259
00:13:41,840 --> 00:13:44,039
will not be infringed upon in any way.

260
00:13:47,520 --> 00:13:48,599
Since we have more than half the votes,

261
00:13:49,080 --> 00:13:50,000
I now announce

262
00:13:51,520 --> 00:13:52,799
that the motion for Chairman Gu Rongchen

263
00:13:53,159 --> 00:13:54,559
to step down as CEO

264
00:13:54,679 --> 00:13:55,359
is passed.

265
00:13:55,880 --> 00:13:56,919
At the same time, in the next

266
00:13:56,919 --> 00:13:57,880
shareholders' meeting,

267
00:13:58,280 --> 00:14:00,000
we will vote on the change of Chairman.

268
00:14:01,880 --> 00:14:02,840
Mr. Gu,

269
00:14:07,359 --> 00:14:08,200
you're late.

270
00:14:08,599 --> 00:14:09,359
What are you doing?

271
00:14:09,679 --> 00:14:10,479
What am I doing?

272
00:14:11,200 --> 00:14:12,159
Can't you tell?

273
00:14:13,719 --> 00:14:14,679
I'm helping you

274
00:14:15,159 --> 00:14:16,719
absorb this company in advance.

275
00:14:18,080 --> 00:14:18,960
Helping you,

276
00:14:19,479 --> 00:14:20,520
and helping myself.

277
00:14:21,479 --> 00:14:22,559
It's a win-win.

278
00:14:23,039 --> 00:14:25,039
You have no right to bypass me

279
00:14:25,919 --> 00:14:27,039
and make such a decision.

280
00:14:29,080 --> 00:14:29,880
We will settle

281
00:14:31,159 --> 00:14:32,520
this score later.

282
00:14:42,119 --> 00:14:42,840
Rongchen,

283
00:14:44,599 --> 00:14:45,840
you... you're...

284
00:14:46,239 --> 00:14:48,080
What are you doing all dressed up?

285
00:14:48,479 --> 00:14:49,359
Going back to the company.

286
00:14:49,440 --> 00:14:50,520
Back to the company?

287
